Bank shall keep adequate records and books of account with respect to its transactions relating to the Program, in which proper entries reflecting all of Bank&#8217;s financial transactions relating to the Program are made in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles.  All such Bank records, files and books of account transactions relating to the Program shall be in all material respects complete and correct and shall be maintained in accordance with good business practice and Applicable Laws.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(h)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;[*]</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">10.05&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Insurance</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Throughout the Term and for [*] thereafter, Bank shall maintain, at its own cost and expense, (i)&#160;statutory workers&#8217; compensation covering all federal, state, or local requirements; (ii)&#160;commercial general liability, including coverage for completed operations, products liability, contractual and personal </font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">42</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s18f32a2900f24d349539fddfc81f97e9"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;padding-left:336px;font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:9pt;">[*] Indicates confidential portions omitted pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed separately with the Commission</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">injury with a minimum limit of [*], (iii)&#160;automobile liability insurance coverage with a minimum limit of [*], and (iv)&#160;excess liability insurance coverage of [*].  The policies of insurance described in this Section&#160;10.05(a) shall be written on an occurrence basis and may be effected through blanket coverage carried by Bank&#8217;s Affiliates.  The carrying by Bank of the insurance required herein shall in no way be interpreted as relieving Bank of any other obligations it may have under this Agreement.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Bank shall, at all times during the Term, provide a certificate or memorandum of insurance naming Costco as an additional insured.  The limits in this Agreement shall be those stipulated.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;With respect to any other insurance available to Costco, Bank&#8217;s insurance shall be primary only in circumstances where the claims or losses arise from Bank&#8217;s negligence with respect to or in connection with the Program and, for the avoidance of doubt, in the event of such claims, Costco shall not be required to make any claim against its own insurance policies before making a claim against Bank&#8217;s policy as an additional insured.  To such extent, any insurance policies maintained by Costco are excess and noncontributory to those policies maintained by Bank.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">10.06&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Change in Law</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If a Change in Law occurs, the Party affected by such Change in Law (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Impacted Party</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;) shall provide notice to the other Party (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Non-Impacted Party</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;), which notice shall describe in detail the applicable Change in Law and the provision or provisions of this Agreement affected by such Change in Law.  Upon the receipt of such notice by the Non-Impacted Party, the Parties shall enter into good faith negotiations for a period of not less than ninety (90)&#160;days as part of an effort to amend this Agreement to reduce or negate the impact of such Change in Law (a </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Change in Law Amendment</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;).  During such period, each Party shall work in good faith to enter into such Change in Law Amendment on terms that alter this Agreement in the minimum way required to accommodate the Change in Law.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If the Parties do not enter into a Change in Law Amendment during such ninety (90)&#160;day period, the Non-Impacted Party may request an additional ten (10)&#160;day period for the senior executives of Costco and Bank to seek to resolve the dispute and enter into a Change in Law Amendment.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;In the event the Parties are unable to enter into a Change in Law Amendment, then at any time during the thirty (30)&#160;day period after the discontinuation of the good faith negotiations regarding such Change in Law Amendment, the Non-Impacted Party shall have the right, at its election, to waive the Impacted Party&#8217;s performance of those provisions of this Agreement which the Impacted Party is unable to perform as a result of the Change in Law (a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Change in Law Waiver</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;).  If the Non-Impacted Party elects to exercise the Change in Law Waiver, the Non-Impacted Party shall provide written notice to the Impacted Party and, as of the date of receipt of the Change in Law Waiver, those provisions of this Agreement that cannot be performed by the Impacted Party shall be waived by the Non-Impacted Party for as long as Applicable Law continues to prevent the performance by the Impacted Party.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;">ARTICLE 11</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;">CONFIDENTIALITY</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">11.01&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;General Confidentiality.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;For purposes of this Agreement, &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Confidential Information</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221; means any of the following:  (i)&#160;information that is provided by or on behalf of either Costco or Bank to the other Party or its agents in connection with the Program or in connection with the transactions contemplated by this Agreement (including information provided prior to the date hereof or the Program Effective Date); (ii)&#160;information about Costco or Bank or their Affiliates, or their respective businesses, customers, members and </font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">43</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s18f32a2900f24d349539fddfc81f97e9"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;padding-left:336px;font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:9pt;">[*] Indicates confidential portions omitted pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed separately with the Commission</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">employees, that is otherwise obtained by the other Party in connection with the Program, in each case including:  (A)&#160;information concerning marketing plans, objectives and financial results; (B)&#160;information regarding business systems, methods, processes, financing data, programs and products and the terms and features and tests thereof; (C)&#160;information unrelated to the Program obtained by Costco or Bank in connection with this Agreement, including by accessing or being present at a non-public business location of the other Party; and (D)&#160;proprietary technical information, including source codes; (iii)&#160;the terms and conditions of this Agreement; and (iv)&#160;the Marketing Plan.  The provisions of this Article&#160;11 governing Confidential Information shall not govern Personal Information, Cardholder Data, Co-Branded Card Account Data, Other Costco Data, or Costco Shopper Data, which shall be governed by the provisions of Article&#160;6.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The restrictions on disclosure of Confidential Information under this Article&#160;11 shall not apply to, with respect to Costco or Bank, information that:  (i)&#160;is already rightfully known to such Party at the time it obtains Confidential Information from the other Party; (ii)&#160;is or becomes generally available to the public or others in the industry other than as a result of disclosure in breach of this Agreement or any other confidentiality obligations; (iii)&#160;is lawfully received on a non-confidential basis from a third party authorized to disclose such information without restriction and without breach of this Agreement; (iv)&#160;is contained in publicly available records or products; (v)&#160;is required to be disclosed by Applicable Laws (provided that the Party subject to such Applicable Laws shall use reasonable efforts to avoid such disclosure and notify the other Party of any such use or requirement prior to disclosure of any Confidential Information obtained from the other Party in order to afford such other Party an opportunity to seek a protective order to prevent or limit disclosure of the Confidential Information to third Parties; provided, further, that such information shall be disclosed only to the extent required by such Applicable Laws); or (vi)&#160;is developed independently by Costco or Bank without the use of any proprietary, non-public information provided by the other Party under this Agreement.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The terms and conditions of this Agreement and the Marketing Plan shall be included in the Confidential Information of both Costco and Bank.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(d)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Subject always to Costco&#8217;s rights to use and share information pursuant to Article&#160;13, if Costco or Bank receives Confidential Information of the other Party (including its Affiliates or their respective businesses or employees) (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Receiving Pa</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">rty</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;), the Receiving Party shall do the following with respect to the Confidential information of the other Party (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Disclosing Party</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;):  (i)&#160;keep the Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party secure and confidential; (ii)&#160;treat all Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party with the same degree of care as it accords its own Confidential Information, but in no event less than a reasonable degree of care; and (iii)&#160;implement and maintain commercially reasonable physical, electronic, administrative and procedural security measures, including commercially reasonable authentication, access controls, virus protection and intrusion detection practices and procedures.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">11.02&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Use and Disclosure of Confidential Information.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Each Receiving Party shall use the Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party only for the purpose of performing its obligations or enforcing its rights with respect to the Program or as otherwise expressly permitted by this Agreement, and shall not make use of such Confidential Information for any other purpose.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Subject always to Costco&#8217;s rights to use and share information pursuant to Article&#160;13, each Receiving Party shall:  (i)&#160;limit access to the Disclosing Party&#8217;s Confidential Information to those employees, authorized agents, vendors, consultants, service providers, accountants, advisors and subcontractors and Governmental Authorities who have a reasonable need to access such Confidential Information in connection with the Program, the sale of Program Assets or other assets of a Party and its Affiliates or the </font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">44</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s18f32a2900f24d349539fddfc81f97e9"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;padding-left:336px;font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:9pt;">[*] Indicates confidential portions omitted pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed separately with the Commission</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">establishment of a new Co-Branded Card or other program or arrangement, in each case, in accordance with the terms of this Agreement; and (ii)&#160;ensure that any Person with access to the Disclosing Party&#8217;s Confidential Information agrees to be bound by the provisions of this Article&#160;11.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">11.03&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Unauthorized Use or Disclosure of Confidential Information.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Each Receiving Party agrees that any unauthorized use or disclosure of Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party will cause immediate and irreparable harm to the Disclosing Party for which money damages will not constitute an adequate remedy.  In that event, the Receiving Party agrees that, in addition to any other remedies the Disclosing Party may have, the Disclosing Party shall have the right to apply to any court of competent jurisdiction for and be granted an injunction compelling specific performance by the Receiving Party of its obligations under this Agreement without the necessity of notice posting any bond or other security, and the Receiving Party agrees not to request such bond or other security.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The Receiving Party agrees promptly to advise the Disclosing Party by telephone and in writing via electronic mail and facsimile of any security breach that may have compromised any Confidential Information or of any unauthorized breach, misappropriation, disclosure or use by any Person of the Confidential Information of the Disclosing Party which may come to its attention, and to take all steps at its own expense reasonably requested by the Disclosing Party to limit, stop or otherwise remedy such breach, misappropriation, disclosure or use.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">11.04&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Return or Destruction of Confidential Information.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">Upon the termination or expiration of this Agreement, the Receiving Party shall comply with the Disclosing Party&#8217;s reasonable instructions regarding the disposition of the Disclosing Party&#8217;s Confidential Information, which may include destruction or return of any and all of the Disclosing Party&#8217;s Confidential Information (including any electronic or paper copies, reproductions, extracts or summaries thereof); provided, however, that the Receiving Party may retain copies of any Confidential Information, including summaries, compilations or analyses thereof to the extent: (a)&#160;required by Applicable Laws; (b)&#160;required by Receiving Party&#8217;s internal document retention and governance policies; or (c)&#160;it would be unreasonably burdensome to destroy (such as archived computer records).  Any Confidential Information retained pursuant to subsections&#160;(a), (b) or (c) shall continue to be treated as Confidential Information subject to the restrictions set forth in this Agreement, notwithstanding any termination or expiration hereof.  The return or destruction of Confidential Information shall not relieve the Receiving Party of its obligations set forth in this Agreement.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;">ARTICLE 12</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">TERM AND TERMINATION</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">12.01&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;TERM AND TERMINATION</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;This Agreement shall be effective on the date hereof, and the Program shall commence on April 1, 2016, or such other date as may be agreed by the Parties (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Program Effective Date</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;).  The term of this Agreement shall commence on the date hereof, and shall continue until the date that is ten (10)&#160;years after the Program Effective Date (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Initial Term</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;); </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">provided</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">however</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">, in Costco&#8217;s sole discretion the Initial Term may be extended by three (3)&#160;years (such that the Initial Term shall be a total of thirteen (13)&#160;years in duration, as measured from the Program Effective Date) upon written notice given to Bank and electing such extension at any time during the Term on not less than [*] prior to the expiration of the then-current Initial Term (an &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Initial Term Extension Notice</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;).  For clarity, and regardless of the </font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">45</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s18f32a2900f24d349539fddfc81f97e9"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;padding-left:336px;font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:9pt;">[*] Indicates confidential portions omitted pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed separately with the Commission</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">relative timing of an Initial Term Extension Notice and a Non-Renewal Notice given pursuant to Section&#160;12.01(b), in the event of a conflict, including a circumstance where a Non-Renewal Notice is given in advance of any Initial Term Extension Notice, the Initial Term Extension Notice shall always govern and control and be binding upon the Parties, and any previously, contemporaneously, or subsequently given Non-Renewal Notice by Bank shall be of no force or effect.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;This Agreement shall be automatically renewed after the Initial Term for successive two (2)&#160;year terms (each a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Renewal Term</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;) unless a Party provides a written notice of non-renewal to the other Party (a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Non-Renewal Notice</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;) not less than [*] prior to the date that is the last day of the Initial Term or any Renewal Term, as the case may be (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Natural Termination Date</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;).  If this Agreement terminates as a result of a Party providing a written notice of non-renewal to the other Party, such termination shall constitute &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Natural Termination</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;.  The twelve (12)&#160;month period prior to the Natural Termination Date shall be known as the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Natural Termination Period</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;.  Additionally, this Agreement may be terminated in accordance with Section&#160;12.02, 12.03 or 12.07 (in each case, such termination shall constitute &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Early Termination</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;).</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">12.02&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Early Termination by Costco.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">If a Bank Termination Event occurs, then, within sixty (60)&#160;days after the expiration of any applicable cure period with respect to such Bank Termination Event, Costco may terminate this Agreement by delivering a written notice to Bank (a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Notice of Termination</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;), which termination shall take effect on the date specified in the Notice of Termination delivered by Costco but in any event no later than twelve (12)&#160;months after the date of delivery of the notice..  The period of time between the date on which Costco provides written Notice of Termination to Bank of its intention to terminate and the date on which this Agreement is terminated shall be the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Costco Termination Pe</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">riod</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, if Notice of Termination is provided by pursuant to terms of Section&#160;12.04(d) or 12.05(d), termination shall take effect five (5)&#160;days after Costco&#8217;s delivery of such Notice of Termination to Bank.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">12.03&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Early Termination by Bank.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:41px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">If a Costco Termination Event occurs, then, within sixty (60)&#160;days after the expiration of any applicable cure period with respect to such Costco Termination Event, Bank may terminate this Agreement by delivering a written notice to Costco, which termination shall take effect on the date that is twelve (12)&#160;months after the date of delivery of the notice.  The period of time between the date on which Bank provides written notice to Costco of its intention to terminate and the date on which this Agreement is terminated shall be the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Bank Termination Period</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, if Notice of Termination is provided by pursuant to terms of Section&#160;12.04(d), termination shall take effect five (5)&#160;days after Bank&#8217;s delivery of such Notice of Termination to Costco.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">12.04&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Mutual Termination Events.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">The occurrence of any one or more of the following events shall, subject to Section&#160;12.07, constitute a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Termination Eve</font><font Section&#160;12.05(h), or a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Costco Termination Event</font><font Such Party also shall promptly notify the other Party when the Force Majeure Event terminates or no longer adversely affects its ability to perform under this Agreement.  The obligations of the Party giving notice, so far as they are affected by the Force Majeure Event, shall be suspended during, but not longer than, the continuance of the Force Majeure Event, and any failure to perform or adhere to any obligation or covenant hereunder shall not constitute a Termination Event, Bank Termination Event, or Costco Termination Event, as applicable.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If a Force Majeure Event materially affects either Party's performance under this Agreement and exists for thirty (30) consecutive days, then the Party that is not subject to such Force Majeure Event shall have the right to terminate this Agreement on not less than twelve (12)&#160;months&#8217; prior written notice to the other Party without further liability, cost or obligation to other Party (other than as provided herein) and such termination shall constitute a Natural Termination for the purposes of this Agreement.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">12.08&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Termination of Exclusivity.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">If Costco delivers a notice of Early Termination pursuant to Section&#160;12.02 or a notice of termination pursuant to the occurrence of a persisting Force Majeure Event pursuant to Section&#160;12.07(b), then, in addition to any other rights available to Costco, Costco shall thereafter have the right, exercisable immediately upon prior written notice to Bank, to elect that the provisions of Section&#160;2.04 shall cease to apply to Costco and, accordingly, Costco and its Affiliates shall be entitled to (i)&#160;issue a Comparable Co-Branded Card for acceptance at Costco Outlets; and/or (ii)&#160;in conjunction with any other card issuer, association or network issue, market, or co-brand any Comparable Co-Branded Card for acceptance at Costco Outlets.  In the event that Costco elects to exercise such right to terminate exclusivity pursuant to this Section&#160;12.08, then Bank may elect to discontinue originating new Co-Branded Card Accounts upon written notice to Costco.  If Bank delivers a notice of Early Termination pursuant to Section&#160;12.03 or a notice of termination pursuant to the occurrence of a persisting Force Majeure Event pursuant to Section&#160;12.07(b), then, in addition to any other rights available to Bank, Bank shall thereafter have the right, exercisable immediately upon prior written notice to Costco, to elect that the provisions of Section&#160;2.06 cease to apply to Bank and its Affiliates.  For clarity, if either Party sends a termination notice but thereafter elects not to terminate, the applicable exclusivity provisions will be reinstated as of the date of such election.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">any Notice of Termination pursuant to Section&#160;12.02).  Bank covenants and agrees that it shall cooperate in all such efforts by Costco, as reasonably requested and instructed by Costco.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Parties will cooperate to reconcile returns, address customer service issues and any other transitional matters relating to planning and implementing any Replacement Program.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">13.02&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Costco&#8217;s Right to Request Information Regarding the Program Assets.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Costco may request in writing that Bank deliver to Costco such information regarding the Program, the Co-Branded Accounts and Co-Branded Cardholders as is set out on </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">Schedule&#160;13.02(a)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">.  For clarity, this request may be made [*].</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If Costco requests in writing that Bank delivers to Costco such information regarding the Program, the Co-Branded Accounts, and Co-Branded Cardholders as is set out on Schedule 13.02(a), then Bank will deliver to Costco the requested information within [*] following receipt by Bank of Costco&#8217;s written request for such information.  Costco may share any such information with prospective New Card Issuers provided that any such prospective New Card Issuer must execute a customary confidentiality agreement satisfactory to Costco prior to receiving any such information and such customary confidentiality agreement must name Bank as a third party beneficiary.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Bank will also provide the information on </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">Schedule&#160;13.02(c)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;to any appraiser designated pursuant to </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">Schedule&#160;1.01(f)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#32;and will deliver such information (and such other information as reasonably requested by the appraisers) to such appraiser no later than [*] following written receipt by Bank of such request from Costco, provided that any such appraiser must first execute Bank&#8217;s customary confidentiality agreement with Bank.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">13.03&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Costco&#8217;s Right to Purchase the Program Assets; Purchase Price Calculation.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;On and after the date upon which a termination notice is provided in accordance with this Agreement, for any reason, Costco or the New Card Issuer designated by Costco shall have the right (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Purchase Right</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;), but not the obligation, to purchase in accordance with and pursuant to Section&#160;13.04, all of the Program Assets (other than Solicitation Materials) (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Portfolio</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;), on such terms and conditions as are reasonably acceptable to Costco (or such New Card Issuer) and to Bank and as are customary for transactions of similar size and complexity, and for a purchase price equal to the sum of:</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;padding-left:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">[*]</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">13.04&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Mechanics of Exercising Purchase Right.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Either the New Card Issuer, if one has been selected by Costco, or Costco (the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Designated Purchaser</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;) must notify Bank in writing if it intends to purchase the Portfolio, which notification (a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Notification of Intent to Purchase the Portfolio</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;) must be sent to Bank no later than [*] prior to the end of the Term or the Termination Period, as applicable.  Upon receipt from Costco of a Notification of Intent to Purchase the Portfolio and from the Designated Purchaser of an executed confidentiality agreement in a form reasonably determined by Bank, Bank shall [*], provide to the Designated Purchaser (i)&#160;an update to the information on </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">Schedule&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">13.02(a) and the information on </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;text-decoration:underline;">Schedule&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">13.02(c), and (ii)&#160;a master file (with accompanying data dictionary) of the Portfolio accounts which shall include data [*] period preceding the month in which the file is delivered.  In addition, Bank shall provide such other information customary for a transaction of this size and nature as may be reasonably and customarily requested to facilitate the </font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">50</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s18f32a2900f24d349539fddfc81f97e9"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;padding-left:336px;font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:9pt;">[*] Indicates confidential portions omitted pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed separately with the Commission</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">due diligence review by the Designated Purchaser, including customary information pertaining to litigation matters relating to the Portfolio or the Program.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Within [*] following the delivery of the Notification of Intent to Purchase the Portfolio, Bank and the Designated Purchaser shall establish a deconversion plan containing customary provisions for a transaction of such nature.  In connection with such deconversion plan, Bank and Costco shall cooperate reasonably in respect of deconversion issues.  Each Party shall pay its own deconversion expenses, except where a deconversion occurs following the delivery by Party of a notice of Early Termination, in which case [*].</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The sale of the Portfolio will be completed pursuant to a purchase agreement between Bank and the Designated Purchaser containing customary and commercially reasonable representations and warranties, terms, covenants, conditions, [*] costs, and indemnities for a sale of such nature.  Such purchase agreement will be executed within [*] of the delivery of the Notification of Intent to Purchase the Portfolio.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(d)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The purchase shall be completed within [*] after delivery of the Notice of Intent to Purchase the Portfolio; provided, however, that consummation of the purchase shall occur no earlier than the end of the Term or the Termination Period, as applicable.  The date of such completion shall be the &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Program Purchase Date</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#8221;.  The Parties shall, subject to receipt of any necessary regulatory approvals, take actions as may be reasonably required in order to consummate the purchase of the Portfolio as contemplated by this Section&#160;13.04.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">13.05&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Obligations of the Parties if Purchase Option Exercised.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;In connection with effecting the Purchase Right and with respect to the Co-Branded Card Accounts, Bank shall cooperate in such process and shall transfer any and all right to Program interchange fees and any dedicated Program bank identification numbers and dedicated Interbank Card Association numbers to the Designated Purchaser as of the Program Purchase Date.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If a Designated Purchaser elects to purchase the Portfolio as provided in Section&#160;13.03, Bank shall comply with the reasonable instructions of Costco regarding the disposition of information that was obtained by Bank in connection with the Program (including any electronic or paper copies, reproductions, extracts or summaries thereof); provided, however, that Bank may use and disclose such information only in conjunction with the wind-down of the Program, and thereafter may retain such information as may be required by Applicable Laws and Bank&#8217;s policies to be retained, including one archived copy of such material as well as any electronic copy that is automatically retained by Bank&#8217;s backup recovery system, which may be used solely for legal and regulatory purposes, and shall so certify to Costco in writing.  Bank will certify to Costco within [*] of the sale of the Portfolio that it has destroyed all information obtained by Bank in connection with the Program other than the information explicitly excluded in this Section&#160;13.05(b).</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If a Designated Purchaser has entered into a purchase agreement with Bank to purchase the Portfolio pursuant to Section&#160;13.04, then, as of the Program Purchase Date:</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(i)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the Designated Purchaser may directly or indirectly provide credit card products and related services to the Co-Branded Cardholders, former Co-Branded Cardholders and others; and</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(ii)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Bank acknowledges that the Program Assets that are the subject of the purchase shall become the property of Designated Purchaser and that as such, subject to the terms of this Agreement, Bank&#8217;s rights powers and privileges with respect to such Program Assets shall cease.</font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">51</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="s18f32a2900f24d349539fddfc81f97e9"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:right;padding-left:336px;font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:9pt;">[*] Indicates confidential portions omitted pursuant to a request for confidential treatment filed separately with the Commission</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(d)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;After the Program Purchase Date, Bank shall have no further rights in or to any Program-related data, except as provided in Article&#160;11 and Article&#160;6, and excluding any Bank-owned Intellectual Property that is licensed to Costco.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">13.06&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Rights of the Parties if Purchase Option not Exercised.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;In the event that: a notice regarding Natural Termination or Early Termination of this Agreement is delivered pursuant to Section&#160;12.01, 12.02, 12.03, or 12.07 as applicable, and Costco gives written notice that it shall not exercise the Purchase Right, or Costco does not provide a Notification of Intent to Purchase the Portfolio pursuant to Section&#160;13.04(a) within the time period set forth in Section&#160;13.04(a), Costco&#8217;s Purchase Right shall have expired and Costco shall have no further rights whatsoever in the Program Assets except any Other Costco Data and the Costco Marks.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If Costco&#8217;s Purchase Right expires pursuant to Section&#160;13.06(a), then, notwithstanding anything in Section&#160;5.08(a) to the contrary and subject to the terms of the Co-Branded Cardholder Agreement and Applicable Laws, Bank shall have each of the following rights:</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(i)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the right to issue to Co-Branded Cardholders a replacement or substitute credit card (which card must not bear any Costco Mark or other design, logo, trademark, trade dress or service mark confusingly similar thereto) with such characteristics as Bank considers appropriate (the cost of card re-design and re-issue being borne solely by Bank); provided, however, that (i)&#160;Bank shall not issue such a replacement or substitute card in cooperation with, branded by or with any name associated with, any Competitor, and (ii)&#160;Bank shall provide each Co-Branded Cardholder with the option to opt-out of receiving any replacement or substitute credit card or any solicitation from Bank or its Affiliates.  Costco shall be permitted to add an enclosure to the last two (2) billing statements sent prior to the date on which this Agreement is terminated to the effect that the Program will be or has been terminated;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(ii)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the right to sell the Co-Branded Accounts and associated Program Assets to a third party purchaser selected by Bank at a price agreed between Bank and such purchaser; provided, however, that Bank shall not sell the Co-Branded Accounts and associated receivables to or for the benefit of a Competitor or any financial institution that issues or co-brands credit cards together with or on behalf of a Competitor; and</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(iii)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the right to exercise any combination of the rights set forth in subsection&#160;(i) or subsection&#160;(ii) above.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Any exercise by the Bank of its rights pursuant to Section&#160;13.06(b) shall occur [*].  Beginning no earlier than Bank&#8217;s completion of its exercise of its rights pursuant to Section&#160;13.06(b), Bank shall no longer use any of the Costco Marks (or any other trademarks, service marks, trade names, logos or proprietary designations confusingly similar thereto).</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(d)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If Costco&#8217;s Purchase Right expires pursuant to Section&#160;13.06(a), then in no event may Bank, in exercising its rights pursuant to Section&#160;13.06(b), re-brand the Co-Branded Cards retained by Bank with the brand of any Competitor of Costco or otherwise, on a targeted basis, solicit or facilitate the solicitation of Co-Branded Cardholders by any Competitor of Costco.  Specifically, Bank may not enter into any agreement with any Competitor of Costco that is (i)&#160;designed to convert Co-Branded Cardholders to a Competitor&#8217;s co-branded or private label program, or (ii)&#160;otherwise encourage any Co-Branded Cardholder to form a business relationship with a Competitor of Costco, either as part of a program with Bank or otherwise.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><br></font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">52</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;-</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div></div><hr style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(e)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If Costco&#8217;s Purchase Right expires pursuant to Section&#160;13.06(a), then upon termination of this Agreement, Costco shall promptly comply with the reasonable instructions of Bank regarding the disposition of all Co-Branded Card Account Data, Cardholder Data or other Bank-owned information obtained by Costco in connection with the Program (including any electronic or paper copies, reproductions, extracts or summaries thereof); provided, however, that, [*], Costco may use and disclose Co-Branded Card Account Data and Cardholder Data only in the ordinary course to wind down the Program, and thereafter may retain one archived copy of such material as well as any electronic copy that is automatically retained by Costco&#8217;s backup recovery system, which may be used solely for regulatory purposes, and shall so certify to Bank in writing.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;padding-left:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">13.07</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;[*]</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;">ARTICLE 14</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:center;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">EFFECTS OF TERMINATION</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:14px;text-align:left;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-weight:bold;">14.01&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;General Effects.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Subject to the terms of this Agreement, and except as the Parties may mutually agree, all obligations of the Parties shall continue upon the delivery of a notice of Early Termination or non-renewal of this Agreement by either Party, until the later of the end of the Termination Period and, if a Notification of an Intention to Purchase the Portfolio has been given pursuant to Article&#160;13, the Program Purchase Date, including:</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(i)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Costco&#8217;s obligation to accept the Co-Branded Cards at each Costco Outlet and Costco Warehouse; provided, however, Costco, at its option, may elect to discontinue accepting Co-Branded Cards if Bank exercises its rights under Section&#160;13.06(b);</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(ii)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the operation of the Program and servicing of the Co-Branded Card Accounts in good faith and in the ordinary course of their respective businesses including the adherence to the SLAs;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(iii)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the review and processing of Co-Branded Card Applications, the issuing of new Co-Branded Cards and the opening and servicing of Co-Branded Card Accounts consistent with past practices immediately prior to the notice of Early Termination or non-renewal of this Agreement;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(iv)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the payment of compensation as set forth in Article&#160;9; and</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:96px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(v)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the extension of credit on Co-Branded Card Accounts and funding of Eligible Receivables.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;If either Party delivers a notice of Early Termination or non-renewal of this Agreement to the other, the Parties will cooperate in good faith to ensure the orderly wind-down or transfer of the Program, including providing all transition support reasonably requested by the other Party at such rates as were applied for such services during the Term, and otherwise complying with this Article&#160;14 and with Article&#160;13.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;[*]</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;">(d)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The Parties will use good-faith efforts to agree on a communication plan to advise Co-Branded Cardholders and the general public of the impending termination of this Agreement no later than [*] following receipt of any notice of an Early Termination, a Bank Termination Event or a Costco Termination </font></div><br><div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">- </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">53</font><font as to the fact that this Agreement and the Program have been terminated and the alternative arrangements being made by the Parties with respect to the Co-Branded Card Accounts; provided, the statement shall not assert any blame with respect to the termination or offering any opinions or reasons as to the cause of such termination.</font></div><div
